Employee Resource Groups





MyAbilities NetworkMyAbilities Network is an employee resource organization built to foster an environment that recruits, retains, develops, and connects the unique skills and attributes of those who have varied abilities.
https://twitter.com/MyAbilitiesNBCUhttps://www.facebook.com/MyAbilitiesNetwork



Asian Pacific Americans AllianceAsian Pacific Americans Alliance establishes to attract, promote, and retain Asian and Pacific Islander American talent within the company. 
https://twitter.com/apanbcuhttps://www.facebook.com/APANBCU



Black Employee NetworkBlack Employee Network fosters and grows a strong Black employee base with focus on contributing their best - both personally and professionally - to the organization and to the community at large.
https://twitter.com/BEN_NBCUhttps://www.facebook.com/BlackEmployeeNetwork



OUTOUT is the Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender & Straight Ally Employee Alliance. Founded in 1986, we are one of Corporate America's oldest LGBT employee groups.    
https://twitter.com/OUTNBCUniversalhttps://www.facebook.com/OUTNBCUniversal



Women’s NetworkThe Women’s Network fosters professional women development by holding events centered on support of women’s issues, key personal development, mentoring, and educational opportunities.  
https://twitter.com/WomensNetNBCUhttps://www.facebook.com/WomensNetworkatNBCUniversal



UnidosUnidos serves as the premier resource for uniting, educating, and empowering aspiring and accomplished Hispanic professionals.  
https://twitter.com/UnidosNBCUhttps://www.facebook.com/UnidosatNBCUniversal



Veterans NetworkThe Veterans Network fosters a business culture that recognizes, supports, develops and promotes the unique characteristics of veterans throughout NBCUniversal. 
https://twitter.com/NBCUVetNethttps://www.facebook.com/NBCUniversalVeteransNetwork



Young Professionals NetworkYoung Professionals Network (YPN) is a volunteer organization built to foster early-in-career NBCUniversal employees. YPN aims to cultivate and retain these employees by providing professional development opportunities, leadership skills, and innovation-driving initiatives.
https://twitter.com/YPN_NBCUhttps://www.facebook.com/YPN.NBCU



