Parks and resorts[edit]
Main article: Universal Parks & Resorts
NBCUniversal owns or licenses the following parks and resorts:

Universal Studios Hollywood; wholly owned[53]
Universal Orlando; wholly owned[54]
Universal Studios Japan; 51% ownership stake in USJ Co., Ltd.[55]
Universal Studios Singapore; run by Genting Group.[56]

Internet[edit]
The streaming video website Hulu is a joint venture of NBCUniversal, Fox Entertainment Group, ABC (Disney–ABC Television Group),[57] and as of 2016, Turner Broadcasting System (Time Warner).[58] The agreement reached between Comcast and the Federal Communications Commission requires NBCUniversal and Comcast to not exercise any influence on Hulu's operations.[59]




